move.} d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. Qe2 {[%cal Ge2e4,Ge2e8][%csl Re4] Lasker's move, 
leading to a queenless middlegame. It is not very dangerous, but in recent times 
has been tried in some higher level games. The main reason is not the quality of 
5. Qe2, but rather the lack of dangerous options in traditional lines - so White 
tries something else.} Qe7 6. Nc3 Nxc3 7. dxc3 Qxe2+ 8. Bxe2 Nc6 9. Be3 Be7 
{[%cal Bc8d7,Be8g8] This was the slow start of the most exciting game of the 
Berlin Candidates 2018 between Vladimir Kramnik and Fabiano Caruana. Black went 
on to win this game after fantastic complications. This game is an excellent 
example for the fact that you can get interesting positions from seemingly equal 
starts if you are creative enough. Make sure to study this game, it is worth 
it!} *

